                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Describes one methodology correctly but fails to distinguish from the other OR provides vague differences</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>Agile uses short iterative cycles (sprints) where features are developed, tested, and delivered continuously, whereas Waterfall follows a sequential linear process where each phase must be completed before moving to the next. Agile welcomes changes to requirements throughout development, while Waterfall requires detailed requirements to be finalized upfront before development begins.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 3 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 3 (4 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  Explain why the Agile methodology is particularly suitable for projects with changing requirements.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
