                      <li><strong>3 marks:</strong> Explains connection between Agile features and changing requirements but lacks clear cause-and-effect structure</li>
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Identifies some Agile features that help with changes but explanation is incomplete or unclear</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Shows basic understanding of Agile flexibility but fails to connect to changing requirements</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p><strong>Cause-and-effect structure:</strong></p>
                      <p>Agile uses short development sprints (cause), so new requirements can be incorporated at the start of the next sprint without disrupting the entire project timeline (effect). Regular customer feedback sessions occur throughout development (cause), which means changes in user needs are identified early and can be addressed immediately rather than after the project is complete (effect). This iterative approach prevents costly rework that would occur in Waterfall methodology where changes late in development require going back to earlier phases.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 4 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 4 (3 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  Justify why the Waterfall methodology might be preferred for developing safety-critical systems such as aircraft control software.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <details class="mt-6">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-green-50 p-3 rounded text-green-800 font-medium hover:bg-green-100">
                  ðŸ“‹ View Marking Criteria & Sample Answer
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
                  <div class="mb-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Marking Criteria:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li><strong>3 marks:</strong> Justifies Waterfall for safety-critical systems with specific reasons (e.g., thorough documentation for compliance, comprehensive testing, formal approval processes)</li>
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Provides valid reasons for using Waterfall in safety-critical contexts but lacks specific connection to safety requirements</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Shows basic understanding of Waterfall benefits but fails to connect to safety-critical system needs</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>Waterfall's sequential approach ensures thorough documentation and formal approval at each phase, which is essential for meeting aviation safety regulations and audit requirements. The extensive testing phase allows for comprehensive safety validation before deployment, reducing the risk of critical failures. The structured approach makes it easier to track and verify that all safety requirements have been properly implemented, which is crucial when human lives depend on the system's reliability.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 5 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 5 (2 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  Identify two advantages of using version control systems in software development projects.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <details class="mt-6">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-green-50 p-3 rounded text-green-800 font-medium hover:bg-green-100">
                  ðŸ“‹ View Marking Criteria & Sample Answer
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
                  <div class="mb-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Marking Criteria:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Correctly identifies two distinct advantages of version control systems</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Identifies one advantage of version control systems OR provides relevant but incomplete information</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>â€¢ Track changes and maintain history of all modifications</p>
                      <p>â€¢ Enable collaboration between multiple developers</p>
                      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 italic">Other acceptable answers: Backup and recovery, Branch management, Revert to previous versions, Merge conflict resolution</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
