              </details>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 6 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 6 (4 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  Explain how code reviews contribute to software quality in development projects.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <details class="mt-6">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-green-50 p-3 rounded text-green-800 font-medium hover:bg-green-100">
                  ðŸ“‹ View Marking Criteria & Sample Answer
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
                  <div class="mb-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Marking Criteria:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li><strong>4 marks:</strong> Explains how code reviews contribute to software quality with clear cause-and-effect relationships (e.g., multiple reviewers â†’ early bug detection; knowledge sharing â†’ improved team skills)</li>
                      <li><strong>3 marks:</strong> Identifies ways code reviews improve quality but lacks clear cause-and-effect explanations</li>
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Shows understanding of code review benefits but explanation is incomplete or vague</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Demonstrates basic knowledge of code reviews but fails to connect to quality improvement</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>Code reviews involve other developers examining code before it is merged into the main project (cause), which leads to early detection of bugs, security vulnerabilities, and logic errors (effect). Multiple developers reviewing the same code brings different perspectives and expertise (cause), resulting in identification of potential improvements and adherence to coding standards (effect). This collaborative process also facilitates knowledge sharing between team members (cause), which improves overall team skill level and ensures consistent code quality across the project (effect).</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
